  "prompt": "How can I remove the HTC One X System folder, which still appears on my Windows 7 list of devices?",
  "response": "To remove the HTC One X system folder from your Windows 7 list of devices, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Disconnect the Device:**\n   Ensure that your HTC One X is not connected to your computer via USB.\n\n2. **Open Device Manager:**\n   - Click on the `Start` menu.\n   - Type `Device Manager` in the search box and press Enter. You might need administrative privileges to access this.\n\n3. **Locate the HTC One X:**\n   In the Device Manager, look for any entries related to your HTC One X under categories like \"Portable Devices,\" \"Universal Serial Bus controllers,\" or \"Other devices.\"\n\n4. **Uninstall the Device:**\n   - Right-click on the HTC One X entry.\n   - Select `Uninstall` from the context menu.\n   - If there's an option to delete the driver software for this device, check that box as well before confirming the uninstallation.\n\n5. **Remove Device from Devices and Printers:**\n   - Open `Control Panel`.\n   - Go to `Devices and Printers`.\n   - Find the icon for the HTC One X.\n   - Right-click on it and select `Remove device`.\n\n6. **Clean Up System Files and Registry (Optional):**\n   - Open `File Explorer`.\n   - Navigate to `C:` drive and look for any remaining folders or files associated with HTC, such as in `Program Files` / `Program Files (x86)`.\n   - You may also want to clean up any related registry entries (use this step cautiously).\n\n   **Note:** Editing the registry can be risky. Ensure you have a backup and know exactly what changes you're making.\n\n7. **Restart Your Computer:**\n   Restart your computer to ensure all changes take effect.\n\nFollowing these steps should remove the HTC One X system folder and any associated entries from your Windows 7 devices list.",
